scp important.txt ubuntu@192.168.1.30:/home/ubuntu/transferred.txt ## Secure copy, or SCP, is just that -- a means of securely copying files. 
Unlike the regular cp command, this command allows you to transfer files between two computers using the SSH protocol to provide both authentication
and encryption.
Working on a model of SOURCE and DESTINATION, SCP allows you to:

Copy files & directories from your current system to a remote system
Copy files & directories from a remote system to your current system




